  "short_description": "(8) GbE RJ45 ports, (1) 1G SFP port, 110W PoE supply, AC/DC adapter included, Wall-mountable kit included",
  "description": "Ideal for wireless ISP (WISP) deployments, the UISP™ Router is a fanless PoE router featuring (8) GbE RJ45 ports and (1) 1G SFP port for an additional fiber uplink option. The UISP Router provides a cost-effective routing solution for WISPs looking to quickly and inexpensively deliver Gigabit wireless speeds to their customers. With its hefty 110W total PoE supply, the UISP Router delivers substantial power to every radio in your service network. The UISP Router is managed with the UISP application, a centralized platform where you can monitor and manage all of your UISP devices. The device is fanless and using thermal cooling for silent operation.",
  "detailed_description": [
    {
      "heading": "Gigabit PoE router for MicroPoP applications",
      "text": "Ideal for wireless ISP (WISP) deployments, the UISP™ Router is a fanless PoE router featuring (8) GbE RJ45 ports and (1) 1G SFP port for an additional fiber uplink option. The UISP Router provides a cost-effective routing solution for WISPs looking to quickly and inexpensively deliver Gigabit wireless speeds to their customers. With its hefty 110W total PoE supply, the UISP Router delivers substantial power to every radio in your service network. The UISP Router is managed with the UISP application, a centralized platform where you can monitor and manage all of your UISP devices. The device is fanless and using thermal cooling for silent operation."
    },
    {
      "heading": "UISP application support",
      "text": "Bluetooth-powered setup via the UISP Mobile app is available. Thanks to UISP app you can centrally manage your networks and clients with ease. Simply organize your clients' plans, setup billing and invoicing, and grow your customer base. UISP application allows viewing network topology, advanced data analytics, quickly set up devices and manage them on the go with a powerful mobile app. Managed with the UISP application: Version 1.4.0-beta.11 and later."
    }
  ],
